Volume Sheet 16

1.    1.Right Click on Sales and select Duplicate. Change the name of the sheet to Volume


 

2.Remove Sales and YoY Sales from the Row shelf 

3. Let the date dimension be there in the column shelf.  



4. Drag and drop Volume Measure to the Row shelf . Under Marks card select Bar

5. Drag and drop YoY Volume calculated field to the Rt side of Volume when you see dotted line drop the YoY Volume .



6. In the column shelf Rt click the YoY Volume and select Mark Type to Line. Select the legend on the top right side right click and select edit color for Total volume select Green color and YoY Vol select Blue color.





7. Select YoY Volume in the Row Shelf right click and select Format , Axis , Numbers ,Percentages , Decimal places 0.





 8. In the work sheet right click on then right axis  YoY vol axis > Edit Axis and erase the title



9. In the work sheet select  Left Axis Total Volume right click on the axis > Edit Title and erase the title


10. Right click  title and select Edit Title Erase the text and enter Volume .Change the font to Tableau Semi bold , Font size to 10 , Font Color Black , Alignment Left




11. Click on YoY Vol in the row shelf hold control button and drag and drop it in the text box. Right click and select format , Numbers , Percentages and Decimal places 0.
